":"Named for her mother Candace Sage Gilbert, who died in 1805."}],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Died at forty-three from her husband's trade","body":"Candace died at age forty-three in 1835 — one year after her husband Solomon Churchill Jr., a tinsmith. Family record attributes both deaths to the mercury used in tin manufacturing. Together they had traveled town to town selling their wares, with their five children left orphaned in 1835."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909"},{"short":"FamilySearch — Hooker Gilbert family tree","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/tree/person/KP4S-SW7"},{"short":"Find a Grave — Christian Lane Cemetery","url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/103278/christian-lane-cemetery"},{"short":"WikiTree (online genealogy)","url":"https://www.wikitree.com/"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"candace-churchill-1791"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM236","primary_name":"Rock Island Memorial Park Cemetery","location":{"city":"Rock Island","county":"Rock Island","state":"Illinois","country":"United States"},"find_a_grave_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/106861/rock-island-memorial-park-cemetery","hooker_connections":["HD3564","HD3565","HD3568","X02730","X02731"],"notes":"Resting place of three consecutive generations of Herbert Churchills: Herbert Jenkins (HD3564, 1881-1934), his son Herbert Jenkins Jr. (HD3565, 1911-1977), and grandson Herbert J. III (HD3568, 1931-2006). Also Dora Mary Wood Churchill (X02730) and Edna Mae Ritchey Churchill Straub Weyant (X02731)."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}